        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">The <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">damage_cooldown</code> counts down each frame. When it hits 0, the player can take damage again.</p>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 2: The Enemy class</h3>

        <pre class="bg-[#1a1a2e] border-2 border-[#00ffcc] rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto" style="box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,255,204,0.2);"><code class="text-gray-200 text-sm font-mono">class Enemy:
    def __init__(self, x, y, enemy_type):
        self.x = x
        self.y = y
        self.enemy_type = enemy_type
        self.move_timer = 0

        if enemy_type == &quot;zombie&quot;:
            self.color = (0, 180, 0)      # Green
            self.health = 3
            self.move_delay = 30           # Moves every 30 frames
        elif enemy_type == &quot;skeleton&quot;:
            self.color = (220, 220, 220)   # White-ish
            self.health = 5
            self.move_delay = 20           # Moves every 20 frames</code></pre>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 3: Enemy movement</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">The <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">update()</code> method is where the AI lives. Zombies pick random directions, skeletons chase the player.</p>

        <pre class="bg-[#1a1a2e] border-2 border-[#00ffcc] rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto" style="box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,255,204,0.2);"><code class="text-gray-200 text-sm font-mono">def update(self, tile_map, player):
    self.move_timer += 1
    if self.move_timer &lt; self.move_delay:
        return

    self.move_timer = 0
    dx, dy = 0, 0

    if self.enemy_type == &quot;zombie&quot;:
        direction = random.choice([(0, -1), (0, 1), (-1, 0), (1, 0)])
        dx, dy = direction
    elif self.enemy_type == &quot;skeleton&quot;:
        if player.x &gt; self.x:
            dx = 1
        elif player.x &lt; self.x:
            dx = -1
        elif player.y &gt; self.y:
            dy = 1
        elif player.y &lt; self.y:
            dy = -1

    new_x = self.x + dx
    new_y = self.y + dy
    if tile_map[new_y][new_x] == 0:
        self.x = new_x
        self.y = new_y</code></pre>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">Notice the skeleton only moves in one direction at a time -- it picks horizontal first, then vertical. This makes it beeline toward you but not move diagonally.</p>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 4: Collision with the player</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">In the Game&#x27;s <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">update()</code> method, check if any enemy is on the same tile as the player:</p>

