pygame.draw.rect(screen, (0, 80, 160), (10, 35, int(100 * cooldown_ratio), 8))</code></pre>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">When the bar is empty, you can swing again.</p>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">The Full Game</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">The complete file is saved as <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">dungeon.py</code> in this folder. It has the full combat system with all the visual effects.</p>

        <h2 class="font-['Bangers'] text-2xl text-[#ffcc00] border-b-4 border-dashed border-[#ff00ff30] pb-2 mt-10 mb-4">Run It!</h2>

        <pre class="bg-[#1a1a2e] border-2 border-[#00ffcc] rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto" style="box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,255,204,0.2);"><code class="text-gray-200 text-sm font-mono">python3 dungeon.py</code></pre>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">Walk around with arrow keys. Press <strong class="text-white">Space</strong> to attack in the direction you&#x27;re facing. You&#x27;ll see a yellow flash on the tile you hit. Enemies flash white when damaged, then flash rapidly and disappear when they die. Your kill count shows in the HUD.</p>

