        <h2 class="font-['Bangers'] text-2xl text-[#ffcc00] border-b-4 border-dashed border-[#ff00ff30] pb-2 mt-10 mb-4">Challenge</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">Create a <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">create_player_sprite_up()</code> and <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">create_player_sprite_down()</code> function that shows the player from behind (walking up) and from the front (walking down). Use them when <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">self.facing</code> is <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">&quot;up&quot;</code> or <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">&quot;down&quot;</code>. Hint: for the &quot;up&quot; version, don&#x27;t draw the eye -- just the back of the helmet.</p>
