        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 4: Music switching</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">Start dungeon music in <code class="text-[#ffcc00] bg-[#ffcc0015] rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold font-mono">__init__</code>, switch to boss music when entering the boss room:</p>

        <pre class="bg-[#1a1a2e] border-2 border-[#00ffcc] rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto" style="box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,255,204,0.2);"><code class="text-gray-200 text-sm font-mono"># In __init__
self.sound.play_music(&quot;dungeon&quot;)

# When entering boss room
if self.current_room == len(self.rooms) - 1:
    self.sound.play_music(&quot;boss&quot;)

# When boss dies or game over
self.sound.stop_music()</code></pre>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 5: Volume controls in handle_input</h3>

        <pre class="bg-[#1a1a2e] border-2 border-[#00ffcc] rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto" style="box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,255,204,0.2);"><code class="text-gray-200 text-sm font-mono">elif event.key == pygame.K_EQUALS or event.key == pygame.K_PLUS:
    self.sound.volume_up()
elif event.key == pygame.K_MINUS:
    self.sound.volume_down()</code></pre>

        <h3 class="font-['Bangers'] text-xl text-[#ff69b4] mt-8 mb-3">Step 6: Volume display in HUD</h3>

